Creating INDEX statement in sql is used to create indexes in tables.
The indexes are used to retrieve data from the database more quickly than others.
The user can not see the indexes, and they are just used to speed up queries/ searches.
Note: 
    ğŸ”¸ Indexes speed up SELECT queries on large tables.
    ğŸ”¸ Indexes slow down INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE because the index also needs to be  
        updated.
    ğŸ”¸ You cannot see the index data, but you can verify it with SHOW INDEX.

Practical:
ğŸ—ï¸ Step 1: Create Database and Use It
    CREATE DATABASE College;
    USE College;

ğŸ“‹ Step 2: Create Table
    CREATE TABLE EMP_INFO (
        ID INT PRIMARY KEY,
        NAME VARCHAR(50),
        DEPT VARCHAR(50),
        SALARY INT
    );

â• Step 3: Insert Sample Data
    INSERT INTO EMP_INFO VALUES
    (101, 'Ravi', 'HR', 6000),
    (102, 'Anita', 'IT', 9000),
    (103, 'Suman', 'Finance', 8500),
    (104, 'John', 'IT', 7500),
    (105, 'Priya', 'HR', 9500);

select * from EMP_INFO;

âš™ï¸ Step 4: Create an Index on SALARY
    Create Index Syntax:
    Create Index <Index_Name> on table (<Column_name>) 

    CREATE INDEX salary_index ON EMP_INFO (SALARY ASC);
    âœ… This index will optimize queries that filter or sort using SALARY.

ğŸ” Step 5: Run an Indexed Query
    SELECT * FROM EMP_INFO WHERE SALARY > 8000;
This query uses the salary_index to retrieve results faster.

ğŸ” Step 6: Create a UNIQUE INDEX
Suppose NAME should be unique:
    CREATE UNIQUE INDEX idx_unique_name ON EMP_INFO(NAME);
    ğŸ›‘ Now if you try to insert a duplicate name, it will throw an error.

    âŒ Try to Insert Duplicate NAME
    -- This will fail because 'Ravi' already exists
    INSERT INTO EMP_INFO VALUES (103, 'Ravi', 'Finance', 8500);

ğŸ—ï¸ Alternative: Add INDEX While Creating Table
    CREATE TABLE DEPT (
        ID INT,
        NAME VARCHAR(50),
        INDEX idx_dept_name(NAME)
    );

ğŸ“– Step 7: View All Indexes on a Table
    SHOW INDEX FROM EMP_INFO;

âŒ Step 8: Drop an Index
    DROP INDEX salary_index ON EMP_INFO;
    DROP INDEX idx_unique_name ON EMP_INFO;
